134. an tu reris, etc.: i.e. (am Ι not right in my interpretation of the matter ?) or do you suppose that Orestes went mad only after killing his mother? The Stoic doctrine makes all criminal conduct evidence of insanity in itself. In fact, after his crime, Orestes did nothing that could be called insane at all. All this goes to prove the Stoic doc- trine, that all misconduct is insane.
